Check if your application has hard-coded users. Verify that your application's code base does not contain any hard-coded users. A hard-coded user is a username and password that is initialized to a fixed value when your application starts. For example:
      string user = "test002";char[] pass = {'p','a','s','s'};
      or 
      string user = "test002";char[] pass = "pass".ToCharArray();
      Common locations to look for hard-coded users include: authentication procedures, authorization procedures, procedures that involve change of privileges, and components that require access controls.
